			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1857')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=40537&TOPIC_ID=5382&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Pulling+Spiders+in+Nurga+%2D+Bleh&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">If you are below 44 I wouldn't even worry about that spider spawn.  There are 2 more sets of 2 closer to the FM zone where the Ogre doesn't even come into play.  Get the map from eqatlas.com to see where the different spawns are. For the other 2 spawns I would use root/dot method (I didn't go there until 45).  I would pull with darkness from around a corner where I could only see 1 of the spiders.  Sometimes (50% or so) Only 1 of them will come.  If that happens then just let it come out a little and root/dot.  At 45 I used Asstytole and VC.  I would let Asstytole wear off and then send the pet in.  You may have to root more than once.  If you pull both.  Root the one you have darknessed ASAP.  Target the other and send pet.  Then dark/root/Asstytole/VC.  Then go back and Asstytole the first one again and reroot.  The one your pet is on should almost be dead now.  Once it dies, try to keep the other one alive for a while.  This will let your pet heal itself and spread out the spawn. I've heard you can fear kite in there but have not tried it.  The spiders are on a 16-18min spawn so handling 4 pre-44 would be plenty.</P><P>If you are above 44 and want the other 2 near the Ogre then just send pet on Ogre, darkness and VC to replenish.  Ogre is only lvl 30 or so so your 44 pet will rip through it.  He's on a 2 hour spawn timer.  I also think he's part of the monk epic quest so someone may need him up.  I had all 3 spawns going for pretty much non-stop killing during 45 and got through it in about 10 hours.</P><P>Oh, one last thing, if you are at 44, have DMF up at all times.  Their poison 1can be nasty.  I wasn't poisoned once with DMF up, but did get poisoned once without it.  The poison killed me after battle even though I had VC up.</P><P><BR>Wurtin</P><P>46th lvl of E'ci<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
