        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Also remember that the pathing can be used to your advantage in the ogre area. Once the big ugly is out of the way, when you pull move over to where he was sitting until the spider s come out of cave then head directly to the wall with the tunnel leading to the two buryni spawns.  The pathing takes the spiders about 10 seconds to get to you if they start heading to the ogres, tons of time for two roots on the trialing spider if a multi pull or a root and dot .  Just run back to the spot where the ogre was if they get close and the pathing will give you another 10 seconds to cast safe from harm.  </P><P>Too easy.... When your ready for the two burnyi let me know, that is a skll in its self pulling them safely if they are both clerics..... yikes....</P><P>Dian Cryptmaker<BR>On Terris-Thule<BR>Of the Clan Battle Cry<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
