        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=40610&TOPIC_ID=5382&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Pulling+Spiders+in+Nurga+%2D+Bleh&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">What level are you? I did most of 40 here quite easily. Don't go past the ogre. Setup at -1500,-300 between the big cave with 4 goblins and the first two spiders at approximately -1600,0.</P><P>The initial break can be a bit hairy if you get lots of resists but I found the root break works pretty well. Summon a good pet(at 40 the worst pet is always green so I knew), put up steelskin and your best shielding, med to full and haste pet. Root one spidey, put pet on other, darken, VoS and nuke with torbas so it dies as quickly as possible so you are ready for the next. Root will most likely break before the first is dead so be ready to reroot. It doesn't matter if you use all your mana and/or pet dies since you have 17 minutes till repop so use all means necessary to get the break.</P><P>If root gets resisted on the initial break you have enough distance to try one more root. If that fails then FD and let pet die. If FD fails then you have a problem :) Spiders hit very hard, two of them on you will rip through steelskin and tear you to shreds.</P><P>Get as much PR gear as possible because strong poison isn't much fun. If you are unlucky and have to break the spawn where one is a straithbone then it can be very tricky since you have to nullify the straithbone's DS or your pet will die fast and hard. So you have to nullify then root the other very quickly and hope for no resists. I've never had a straithbone land a darkness or fear on me yet(keep shielding up helps with that MR boost) so don't worry about that happening, just get rid of that DS asap.</P><P>Spawn rate with spiders is 17 minutes almost exactly. I got 4 of my yellow bubs there at 40 and only died once when everything went wrong -- two root resists, failed FD and failed FD again argh. I only left because it gets a bit lonely in there. I finished out 40 in OT where you can stay amused by all the inane /ooc chatter lol.</P><P>Good luck, your heart will be pumping out of your chest on your first break attempt but once it's done you can just relax and turn on the TV or read a book in between spawns.</P><P><BR><b>Dravula</b> 41th DE Necro <b>Bertoxxulous</b><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

