        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/18/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 05:00:22</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2002"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2002')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=40985&TOPIC_ID=5382&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Pulling+Spiders+in+Nurga+%2D+Bleh&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I just camped them for 3 days now (43-45 :smokin). Very easy, my 44 pet can almost solo one spider. I cannot buff it or it'll KS me every time.<BR>Most of the spawns are double, you have to deal with 2 spiders at a time. One is always single-pullable and others can be too, but less reliably, just experiment a bit.<BR>I break the spawn usually with ST then run to my pet using the pathing to buy some time (in the first room with the tunnel leading to sleeping ogre, there is 2 spiders in a niche, camp your pet in the middle of room and run to wall opposite to spiders. You can pull these two spiders and the two others in the room behind). I sick pet on spider then root it. Then i run back to STed spider, root it and ST it again. Then back to fight, I darkness (give you enough time to use pathing to your advantage in case you aggroed too much and root spider again), VoS and lifetap. Spiders have a bit over 1500hp. Once you have the 44 pet, it's trivial, you can take 6 spiders in 17 min.<BR>Your 39 pet may not survive the first fight. When you get the ST wore off message, FD once to clean aggro of rooted spider, you'll have plenty of time to rest and make a new pet to kill it. Once you broke the first double spawn, you can do the same on a second double spawn, and XP will be AMAZING.<BR>Other strategies are possible. For example, when in the room I talked about, if feared, spiders will go towards sleeping ogre. Since he's 30, you can easily kill it first (it's a long spawn, 2 hours or something) then fear kite the spiders np, others spiders spawn are far apart and fear will break before the kited spider reach anything.<BR>Also, if your ST was successful and your root on second spider too, before spider hit you and pet aggro on it, just FD and wait for ST to wear off. You are almost guaranteed the STed spider forgot you and can take the rooted one far more easily.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
